":"1478","1442":"1442","1475":"1475","1572":"1572","about 1500":"about 1500","1450":"1450","about 1475":"about 1475","1470":"1470","about 1495":"about 1495","Tolland, Somerset, England, United Kingdom":"Tolland, Somerset, England, United Kingdom","Tolland, Somerset, England":"Tolland, Somerset, England","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Wolcott","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["English (Devon and Surrey): habitational name from Wollacott in Thrushelton (Devon), named from the Old English personal name <i>Wulfnōth</i> + <i>cot</i> ‘cottage, hut, shelter’. This form of the surname is now rare in Britain.","History: Henry Wolcott (1578–1655), clothier, came from Tolland, Somerset, England, and settled in Windsor, CT, in 1636. His grandson Roger (1679–1767) was colonial governor of CT; his great-grandson Oliver (1726–1797) was a signer of the Declaration of Independence."],"variants":[{"name":"Woolcott","meanings":["English: variant of   Wolcott  ."]},{"name":"Woolcock","meanings":["English (Cornwall): probably a variant of   Wolcott  ."]}]},{"name":"William","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Probably the most successful of all the Old French names of Germanic origin that were introduced to England by the Normans. It is derived from Germanic <i>wil</i> ‘will, desire’ + <i>helm</i> ‘helmet, protection’. The fact that it was borne by the Conqueror himself does not seem to have inhibited its favour with the ‘conquered’ population: in the first century after the Conquest it was the commonest male name of all, and not only among the Normans. In the later Middle Ages it was overtaken by   John  , but continued to run second to that name until the 20th century, when the picture became more fragmented."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When William Wolcott was born about 1475, in Tolland, Somerset, England, his father, William Wolcott I, was 26 and his mother, Joan Sperry, was 34. He married Elizabeth Whetchill about 1495, in Tolland, Somerset, England, United Kingdom. They were the parents of at least 2 sons. He died about 1500, in his hometown, at the age of 27."},"et":{"about 1475–about 1500":"umbes 1475–umbes 1500","1475–1500":"1475–1500","1478–1514":"1478–1514","1500–1572":"1500–1572","1450–1501":"1450–1501","1442–1470":"1442–1470","1514":"1514","1501":"1501","1500":"1500","1478":"1478","1442":"1442","1475":"1475","1572":"1572","about 1500":"umbes 1500","1450":"1450","about 1475":"umbes 1475","1470":"1470","about 1495":"umbes 1495","Tolland, Somerset, England, United Kingdom":"Tolland, Somerset, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Tolland, Somerset, England":"Tolland, Somerset, England"},"fi":{"about 1475–about 1500":"noin 1475–noin 1500","1475–1500":"1475–1500","1478–1514":"1478–1514","1500–1572":"1500–1572","1450–1501":"1450–1501","1442–1470":"1442–1470","1514":"1514","1501":"1501","1500":"1500","1478":"1478","1442":"1442","1475":"1475","1572":"1572","about 1500":"noin 1500","1450":"1450","about 1475":"noin 1475","1470":"1470","about 1495":"noin 1495","Tolland, Somerset, England, United Kingdom":"Tolland, Somerset, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Tolland, Somerset, England":"Tolland, Somerset, England"},"fr":{"about 1475–about 1500":"environ 1475–environ 1500","1475–1500":"1475–1500","1478–1514":"1478–1514","1500–1572":"1500–1572","1450–1501":"1450–1501","1442–1470":"1442–1470","1514":"1514","1501":"1501","1500":"1500","1478":"1478","1442":"1442","1475":"1475","1572":"1572","about 1500":"environ 1500","1450":"1450","about 1475":"environ 1475","1470":"1470","about 1495":"environ 1495","Tolland, Somerset, England, United Kingdom":"Tolland, Somerset, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","Tolland, Somerset, England":"Tolland, Somerset, Angleterre","lifeSummary":"Lorsque William Wolcott est né environ 1475, à Tolland, Somerset, Angleterre, son père, William Wolcott I, avait 26 ans et sa mère, Joan Sperry, avait 34 ans. Il a épousé Elizabeth Whetchill environ 1495, à Tolland, Somerset, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni. Ils ont eu au moins 2 fils. Il est décédé environ 1500, dans sa ville natale, à l’âge de 27 ans."},"de":{"about 1475–about 1500":"um 1475–um 1500","1475–1500":"1475–1500","1478–1514":"1478–1514","1500–1572":"1500–1572","1450–1501":"1450–1501","1442–1470":"1442–1470","1514":"1514","1501":"1501","1500":"1500","1478":"1478","1442":"1442","1475":"1475","1572":"1572","about 1500":"um 1500","1450":"1450","about 1475":"um 1475","1470":"1470","about 1495":"um 1495","Tolland, Somerset, England, United Kingdom":"Tolland, Somerset, England, United Kingdom","Tolland, Somerset, England":"Tolland, Somerset, England","lifeSummary":"Als William Wolcott um 1475 in Tolland, Somerset, England geboren wurde, war sein Vater William Wolcott I 26 und seine Mutter Joan Sperry 34. Er hat um 1495 in Tolland, Somerset, England, United Kingdom Elizabeth Whetchill geheiratet. Sie hatten mindestens 2 Söhne. Er starb um 1500 im Alter von 27 Jahren in seinem Geburtsort."},"ht":{"about 1475–about 1500":"about 1475–about 1500","1475–1500":"1475–1500","1478–1514":"1478–1514","1500–1572":"1500–1572","1450–1501":"1450–1501","1442–1470":"1442–1470","1514":"1514","1501":"1501","1500":"1500","1478":"1478","1442":"1442","1475":"1475","1572":"1572","about 1500":"about 1500","1450":"1450","about 1475":"about 1475","1470":"1470","about 1495":"about 1495","Tolland, Somerset, England, United Kingdom":"Tolland, Somerset, Angletè, United Kingdom","Tolland, Somerset, England":"Tolland, Somerset, England"},"hu":{"about 1475–about 1500":"1475 körül–1500 körül","1475–1500":"1475–1500","1478–1514":"1478–1514","1500–1572":"1500–1572","1450–1501":"1450–1501","1442–1470":"1442–1470","1514":"1514","1501":"1501","1500":"1500","1478":"1478","1442":"1442","1475":"1475","1572":"1572","about 1500":"1500 körül","1450":"1450","about 1475":"1475 körül","1470":"1470","about 1495":"1495 körül","Tolland, Somerset, England, U